      "label": "claim"
    },
    "A2": {
      "text": "Maimon maintains that as long as sensibility is regarded as an independent source of cognition to the understanding, the possibility of applying concepts to sensible intuition cannot be comprehended. The connection between the two can only be explained by demonstrating that they both derive from the same cognitive source.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
