      "text": "Maimon's starting point is to distinguish between two types of a priori cognition, that which is pure and a priori, and that which is merely a priori",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "A4": {
      "text": "Cognition that is both a priori and pure does not refer to sensibility in any way, neither to the a posteriori, i.e. to specific sensations, nor to that which constitutes a condition for the sensation of objects, namely, space and time. This type of a priori is completely conceptual.",
      "label": "premise"
